Template: journald-archive/loopback_size_gib
Type: string
Description: Archive disk budget, in GiB:
 journald-archive stores compressed journals in a btrfs loopback file
 mounted at /var/log/journal_archive/. This number is that file's size:
 the maximum *physical* disk space the archive will ever occupy, and the
 only capacity knob you need to set.
 .
 How much history this buys depends on how well your logs compress, which
 is discovered automatically: when the archive fills up, the oldest
 journals are dropped to stay within this budget. Better compression
 simply keeps more history in the same space.
 .
 The suggested default is computed from the current size of
 /var/log/journal/, assuming a conservative 5x compression ratio.
 Increase it for more history; decrease only if disk space is tight.

Template: journald-archive/invalid_size
Type: error
Description: A positive whole number is required
 The size must be a positive whole number of GiB, with no units or other
 characters (for example: 2). Please try again.
